  },
  {
    "message_type": "private",
    "recipient": "Austria",
    "content": "Austria—private: Your situation in the Balkans is fragile. England prefers a weak but intact Austria rather than a chaotic collapse that might empower a continental hegemon. I will not intervene directly in the Adriatic now, but I will oppose any Austrian attempt to reach into Western Europe that jeopardizes Italian or French coasts. Forecast implication: the artifact signals a non-negligible chance (~35%) of opportunistic moves from Austria to relieve pressure; restraint will be rewarded diplomatically. Offer: maintain current fronts and avoid naval provocations; I will refrain from supporting Italian moves against your coast for the immediate season."
